review_text: Great Toddler/Mommy McDs with large, enclosed play place, climbing structure 2y+, ordering/pay station inside play area, high chairs, NO wifi access, bathroom not in play area, & dirty but not horrid. They had pancakes allday in happy meal & lots of parking. I d recommend, if you need a place to work & eat , while children run in circles screaming. There are many screaming children. Kid-friendliness: Bathrooms, enclosed play area, large climbing structure with slide & padded area. 2yr -12yrs, high chairs, room for strollers, trash, bathrooms Wheelchair accessibility: All on one level, handicapped parking, room in restaurant for wheelchairs

This McDonalds has a great location spot next to Science World and the stadium. Surprisingly, it has free parking with a big parking lot. Its open 24/7 for dine in, take out, and drive through. Kid-friendliness: Has an indoor playground

Well the reason Im giving them a 5 star is because there security caught the thief who actually stole the kids meal I had on the table so when I took little man I was looking after to the restroom so guy took his food and his box of doughnuts and actually drank out of my coffee cup but they handled with respect and I appreciated that from them plus the other people around us where super nice
It was fairly quick with a full line up frendly staff on the drive through

Consistently THE WORST drive thru service. I am asked to pull over and wait a minimum of 7 minutes every time I go. And every time, I have to walk in and demand my food...AND every single time the sauces I PAID FOR are not in the bag. The place is an absolute circus with food delivery guys, homeless, bums, addicted people lurking about everywhere. Its a zoo and the service is atrocious. Im DONE.
This Mc Donald center is fully automated. You can customize everything. Large variety in the menu and nice salad that I havent seen in any other branches before.
I have purchased 4 cars from these guys over the years and their service has been outstanding. I highly recommend them to anyone looking for a used car in excellent condition!!!!
Changed my life. The finest 5 star cuisine Ive ever had, how have I never heard of this place? Its like McMagic in my mouth!

In the middle of a heat dome and it was unbelievably hot outside ... walking into the restaurants lovely, air conditioned interior was such a relief! It was crazy busy and totally chaotic but all the staff we dealt with were so friendly and pleasant. There was lots of parking outside and no line-ups at the ordering kiosks and the washroom was spotless. Altogether a great visit.

Clean atmosphere. Not enough staff in the evening, for over a month now there has only been one cashier witch causes slower lines not everybody has a bank card to  pay with online. This also cause customers to get frustrated and angry and even sometimes cause a scene with staff members,  unfortunately One customer was extremely  frustrated he told a staff member to f@#(c) off and the staff member behind the counter said exactly the same words right back to the customer before he walked out.. I have Never experienced this at a McDonalds. Not the staff members fault but if there was more cashiers at the front maybe that could have been avoided.
The place  had a great experience with STAFF and Customers. Very nice,I will go Back.
Quick burger snack for lunch, always fast and tasty
Big place. Clean, I enjoy dine in

Been coming here every Saturday morning for breakfast, and every time I have quality service and food. There are mornings when the line up to the drive-thru is out to the street and we are only in line for 5 mins total and have our food. Other locations have us park and wait 10+ minutes even with no line. All employees work fast but politely. The food is always so fresh and hot. Could not recommend this location enough!
Great customer service. Went their around 12:15 and girl named Amrit took my order. She was really polite and humble. Great customer interaction.
This place is a zoo but they had shamrock shakes in may so they get 5 stars

As with most McDonalds, Ive had varied experiences but ill just share my most recent one as it was excellent.  The line up in the drive through was long and extended onto the street and through the parking lot. I couldnt believe how fast I got through, especially from ordering to payment to receiving my food. I thanked the lady for being so quick, and enjoyed my food which was hot and made how I asked. Yum!
Great food n drinks

Best thing about this particular McDonald would be the staff. From the Paladin guard that is always alert and courteously opens the door for customers to the guys in the kitchen. Ive dined here three times and each time these guys seem to actually enjoy doing their jobs. Big up to them
I got a shamrock McFlurry and it was great but man they gotta do something the atmosphere it felt like I was entering the bowels of the earth.
Good service. Tasty. Modest price
Fast friendly service and exactly what I ordered.  Great work team. Keep up the good work.

Very very friendly, efficient, & quick service. This drive through was what drive throughs should all be like. Correct order taking, very friendly & well spoken, good at up selling products, & making sure the customer gets the food hot, well prepared, & properly bagged. This was my best tasting, & well bagged Double Quarter Pounder with Cheese meal since the 1980s Special Kudos to this worker. Management should recognize her for her abilities & her #1 standards. ********** Stars for her

Its McDonalds the best munchies ever omnomnomn Vegetarian options: Theres beyond meat available Dietary restrictions: Fish allergens peanut allergens Parking: If your a customer you dont have to worry about paying for parking Kid-friendliness: No play place however theres an upstairs where kids can be loud and run around Wheelchair accessibility: Its ground level so no need to find a ramp

For the location and the how clean the restaurant is and the added security. It s a the only place I found that I can bring my small children into where no one is sleeping In the chair s Thanks again the people working in the back are amazing staff.
Today the chicken mcmuffin was the best I have ever had since it they came out both were very fresh. Soft cheese, soft muffin and tender chicken.  Congrats  well done. Keep it up.
I love the self checkout that they have, very convenient and theres never much of a wait even though tons of people were there!
Always got to love the artery clogging slopes that they serve here. May not be good for you but sure does taste delicious

After 1 year of lockdown been ( 2 yrs ) been to McD locations on Main! Have to say it was not a disppointment for an early dinner ( 2Can Dine coupon ). 1/4 pound cheese burger and also bought ( coupon ) 6 mini doughnuts ( acceptable, not the best compare to Cardems,Luckys doughnuts ) but its tasteful. The meals was amazing and its services! Worth the trip/back!
Very fast service . Food was actually put together properly and not sloppy. Like most other restaurants of the same.

Incident from 11th Nov. I wanted to thank the security guard from Paladin working that morning. Tall Indian Guy, He bravely defended us again 2 homeless people who were kicking our car doors and were threating us. He made sure we were safe and kicked them out. Thank you so much. I came to personally thank him multiple times but never saw him after that, as we rushed out that day, we were really scared. Thank you so much for your service.
Drive thru worker. Phenomenal
Great place to eat and love the staff

Used to work here, great people and managers. However dont stay after 10 pm, then its claimed by junkies. Watch for needles in washrooms, bags, crannies, toilet paper dispense. Also once saw a dude in the garbage compactor.
Its fast and good service

Its a McDonalds, but Im always amazed at how fast the drive through provides service. Good location (for McDonalds, lets not get me wrong here, its not good actual food). I fill my breakfast sandwich needs here regularly.
Best time to come to this location is late at night when theres only several groups dining and not a lot of people in line waiting for their food. The staff are very nice here.

Great service...Id ordered a double Big Mac and when I got to the Van to eat it with Rocky my pitbull...I found just a double burger not 4. I went back and they gave me my proper order and let me keep the double. Rocky real my enjoyed it.
Nice place
I ordered from Uber eats. Incredibly fast! My burger was made to my specifications. Perfectly. Lol thank you for my cookie! An excellent encounter! I love you guys!
The free fries are too good lol.. the new cigarettes
Great for a quick snack any time of the day. Menu as expected.
The staff are so aware and gracious I asked them for additional condiments and they immediately gave me Thank you so much I ll always buy from them

This used to be one of dirtiest McDonalds in north America due to homelessness and people with low personal care in its surroundings.  Washrooms where dirty, a lot of people very spending more than usual time in the lobby. BUT NOW!!!!!!!!! After having doors at its North West entrance closed, and having security at its main entrances, there are no more unrelated people hanging around. Even doordash and uber eats receive their deliveries from the security officer making it even more professional. Now I can tell the management worked hard to re- establish this place. I really hope this place holds their security officer which is very polite and professional. I also hope other McDonalds with busy downtown traffic to employ security officers , especially once covid is over and night clubs re opens.
Very consistent! I think they have yet to mess up my order and Ive visited this location MANY times. Plus the staff are friendly and have a great sense of urgency.
Quiet place. Nice view. For the rest, just an ordinary MacDonalds :)))
It was spectacular. Food elevates mood and the fine dining experience elevated me to hitherto unknown realms of clarity and inner peace.
My first experience with this restaurant was amazing but the location was great and easy for us to find and the price was great

I absolutely love McDonalds coffee and have no shame in saying it! Theyre coffee isnt too hot when you get it, and the taste is just so good! If youre ever looking for just a black coffee and dont want to break the bank..... Orrrr seriously just really want a good coffee, get theirs. I drink mine with 4 cream (yes, always and no it hasnt made me fat haha) I love that I buy 7 coffees and get a free one as well! The food is alright as well if you like carby stuff haha

[REVIEWED IN OCTOBER 2019] This McDonalds is a nice, large, but busy location, with plenty of comfortable seating areas to settle in. I came here & paid so I could use their WiFi to play World of Warcraft. Found out WoW was unplayable for whatever reason, despite other online games working okay. Rated 5 stars despite this disappointment, but its a pretty awesome McDonalds location. 24 hours at that!
It was nice but wierd. A stranger cleared it ,told me I should sit there, I ate my big Mac, ( alone but not) with barriers,I had a covid good time . I guess Today I made it to 59 yrs..

The paladins slinging grease in this citadel of soberiety are the last line of defense against the quarreling, drunken horde stumbling back toward the skytrain after striking out in Gastown. God bless them in their solemn duty.
This McDonalds food was pretty good. I liked my big Mac like I always get.  And always the best after a fat joint...
Great stop when walking along the creek because they have a washroom
Its nice and clean. The staff were all very friendly and helpful. McDonalds does everything right it seems!
This McDonalds is one of the best in Vancouver.  Very friendly and helpful staff provide a very pleasant overall order experience.  Keep up the great work
Nice day

Very sloppy burgers leaves you running straight to the bathroom! UPDATE: Since Ive last left this review. Ive notice that this particular McD has been making their burgers more with care, rather than the sloppy mess that i have been getting from here before.
Good location. Not much different than any other one but they are quick and give great service. Can get crazy busy at some hours.
Very well kept cleanliness of restaurant two thumbs up no mess ups on my order as well another plus

This location is one of the busiest McDonald s in town. I really give the employees credit for staying relatively cheerful throughout the day, even though this location gets quite a colourful variety of patrons.
I went thru the drive thru and it didnt take too long. The food was great service was good.

Oh man. Only come here if youre drunk or high. If youre sober, you better be going through the drive-thru. Otherwise, youll be seeing all the magnificent disgusting people who come here on Friday night on Wednesday afternoon.
Always fast. I order from the app and get it for pick up and its usually ready by the time Im there.
Not really sure why they were nervous during the work
Cause of whip cream on my hot cakes umm good
Very busy but fast service coffee was perfect they made it just right cause I like my coffee on the cold side thanks keep up the good work
Staff are great. They can handle the chaos...  Have always had a good experience here, order is always correct. Staff is kind and helpful
If you have kids. You can dine and let your kids play

The service is really good but the boys washroom is really dirty I am really scared of the washroom but the food and service is very very good the mangers are very nice also the soft serve ice cream that they make is really big and yummy
Excellent fast service. Cleaning person Wednesday am was very friendly and efficient. Meal was hot. Excellent all around outlet.
The seating situation has changed due to covid-19 but the place is very clean and hand sanitizer are everywhere and ready to be used.

Just love the service of this place....   I had a wound on my hand which started bleeding suddenly... So I asked them a band aid... Nd the staff nd the manager was so nice... That they offered me the first aid asap..  thank you so much for your help
Restaurant was clean first friendly service order was correct and served hot and fresh.
For lunch today, I had a Dijon Onion Burger, & it was delicious. It was only $2.99. I should have had two, however, as one wasnt quite enough to satisfy my hunger!
Busy restaurant with large parking lot. Staffs are friendly and efficient. Foods are within the standard. I appreciated and thanks they have a security guard in the restaurant.
Big one, not so clean    but cleaner than most others
Went thru the drive thru and the service was very fast and the staff were polite and they were able to get our whole order correct  :)
Bah dah dah daaah i am lovin it and alittle secret smiles are free;)
In near downtown, this is the best McDonalds. The most I like is, this has parking lot. The cons are you will see lots of homeless, washroom is dirty.
Dont know how long McDonalds have been in town but I was really surprised by how good the dining experience is. I think it will catch on.
Excellent quality control on the chicken nuggets. Consistently deliver a highly nutritious meal.
Busy, basic not trendy but they never let down.. good food and good service.
Food service is awesome and was clean in the dining area. Cant complain at all.
Outside clean washroom clean too good foods chicken  fish so good,coffee  can u make  a little hot drink better thx
Was pretty good they one of the good McDonalds around always clean and they treat the customer like customers no judgemental all
Despite location being somewhat sketchy, this location manages to keep clean and provide good service and food cooked to exacting standards.
Same McDonalds as everywhere. Crazy fast service and automated order kiosks everywhere! Kudos to the staff for being good at handling the local demographics of the DTES area.
probably the most cursed mcdonalds in Vancouver however immensely blessed at the same time
Surprisingly clean, staff must be incredibly patient. Theyve rarely ever messed up my order
The food is good love it its so awesome n the bigmac meal I love the most
Wonderful play structure my kids enjoy. Also, new upstairs dinning area is clean, and airly.
Friendly staff and good cooks. One of the best McDonalds in Greater Vancouver, conveniently located downtown by Science World, Via (train and bus station), Skytrain and close to Chinatown.
Gotta love McDonalds    Food was perfect as usual here too!
Lots of parking spaces. Clean place with security agent always available. Staff are quick and good in service.
All McDonalds are the same however this particular one has the highest ratio of junkie to staff in the Pacific Northwest. Thats a fact.
It was busy but staff were very efficient and organized.
Good location and good service even in the pandemic. Access to washroom too and security personnel by the entrance for assistance.
Dont blame them if youre fat.  They have salad and its not their fault if you dont choose it.
Prices have gone up since covid 19 but good food and good service

I went to McDonalds Still Creek yesterday at around 16:30. It s a nice place with very easy parking. Staff are kind and very professional, service is great! I also noticed that the Drive through is fast as well. Food : 2/5 |

When I took my first sip of the iced coffee that I purchased for $1 it washed away all negative memories of my gambling sessions and all the chicanery that is employed to extract money from me. This iced drink provides me with so much upside while putting down very little capital. Thanks you, I will not be clown shoed again

I dont go to McDonalds very often but this one is my favourite. Very clean, spacious dining area both inside and outside and really fast-paced! My favourite items here are hash browns and chicken MacGuffin. Smoothies are good too especially the ones with mango and pineapple.
Came in for a visit today. I truly appreciate the customer service from Vivick one of the Managers..He went above and beyond. He was kind and helpful. I left beyond satisfied.
Whoever packed my order took the time to write a note about my iced coffee and I really appreciated the service!

I really like sitting on the upper floor with my food. Its has plenty of space to dine in with different table options. It has a separate play place where my kids can play while I am having my coffee. They also have refill station upstairs and Washrooms, accessible washroom is downstairs. They have a separate room for Kids party, I saw birthday decorations and cake one time. It has a lot of parking as well.

As much as I feel empathetic towards the crew members that work here, it s just too busy when you re close to the BCIT on weekdays. Otherwise, the production team is doing amazing. The service is great, the food is decent. Thank you McDonald s.

Mic-ie D so fast so good this location is so big and has been here forever I used to go to this location with my dad when I was little. The place has not changed since I was a kid. Recommendation = Fries + ice cream.       +
$4 combo deal for bacon and egg mcmuffin and medium coffee

This location is big in two floor and has patio seating Relatively clean Staff are kind and understanding. I had some issues with McDonalds app, they helped me with that and actually offered free Coke, fries and one shake to make me happy Convenient parking location and kids play also provided but closed due to Covid

This meal had me feeling like I I I m in the stars tonight. This is getting heavy Can you hear the bass boom? Im ready (woo hoo) Life is sweet as honey Yeah, this beat cha-ching like money, huh Disco overload, Im into that, Im good to go Im diamond, you know I glow up Hey, so lets go. So cheesy BTS joke aside the sauces were actually really good! Substituted the coke that s part of the meal for a coffee Frappuccino and it was very good overall. Staff at the drive through were friendly and efficient. No complaints at all.

McDs is our summer go to.  Got lemonade, kid played in the play area, A/C, inflation friendly if youre ordering off the value menu and use app promos. Only critique is the parking could be scarce depending on the time of day but thats about it. Kid-friendliness: Theres a play place which is partially separated in the upper floor.  Well decorated, very vibrant.  Remember to bring socks.
The best fast food. Quick service with a smile. One of the greatest franchises on earth. The outlet at Still Creek is my favourite! Always get my orders correct and friendly/polite!
One of the coolest McDonalds ever! Lots of bright windows and the place was very clean. Good job staff :)
Great food here. Everything was hot when we received, the restaurant was clean and food tasted great. Didnt have to wait long, and the kids were happy.

I and 3 others just wanted a snack so my oder just z cheese burgers extra pickle, onion, and ketchup, mustard .. Now I know this is small but its what I wanted and for the extra.. Non existent..  Basically now when I get the food I check everything before I leave.
The manager on shift tonight was so kind to us. I wish I had gotten his name but he was wonderful.
Food was excellent and the service is always prompt, friendly. Great place to eat.

This is the best McDonalds i have been to for a very long time. Very quick service the line moved so smooth, food was fresh and hot, order was correct and staff was very friendly. Store front kept very clean.

I had prejudice against McDonalds before until their restaurants changed for good. Every McDonalds now is top notch. Clean, modern...its a pleasure to pass by. A&W and Wendys restaurant  need to start working.
Beautiful and gracefully place for coffee, breakfast. I come here two or three times a week with my wife and friends   . Thanks!
Large popular location with tons of seating. Fully app supported where you can order from your car or from any table you pick. Consistent flavor like what you would expect from any McDonald s.
You guys made my night. And everything was delicious
This is a great location. Standard fast food and ok service but a great location.
Im really sad to get this mcmuffin. Some parts are burned. This muffin is so hard as plastic. I can eat that without muffins. Unfortunately, I got two Mcmuffin... Guess what next happens.

Yesterday morning was quite stressful for McD HQ. It seems as they were having computer/ticket printer issues causing anxious diners to inquire on their order. Glad to witness the miss with the colorful hair still prioritized to help an elderly and his order of five hot beverages to his car. A tip of the cap towards the staff!
Best McDonalds Ive been to. great juicy pattys
One of the best MacDonald in lower mainland, I believe this location is one of their staff training center Kid-friendliness: Kids friendly

Great quick and efficient drive though. Its also good that its close to Freeway and Lougheed Highway so its easy to get back on your traveling route. It can be tricky getting in or out of parking lot. If dinning in can be busy with long wait times.

Nice clean McDonalds.  Very busy location and they do a remarkable job keeping things moving.  Always fresh and golden fries. The parking lot tends to get flooded during rain storms. Lots of seating area.  The ordering and waiting area is too small for the volume they do.  The upstairs area is a good spot to enjoy your McDonalds.
It is good place to stay for relax.

I dont mean the quality is bad but the size. That apply to all McDonalds. Food is not worth. I only buy coffee but coffee quality is not stable. Other McDonalds are the same. Sometimes, I got just brown water without any coffee taste.

Did not grab her name but the lady that was working today around 12-1P, who was particularily stocking the straws, lids, and cleaning the trays deserves a lot more credit and appreciation than people show her. Yes, its simple tasks but a task / role that many overlook, perhaps including this company itself. As shes most likely just another sin number on a piece of paper to most. In truths, its because its a simple task and many consider it needy and the right / entitlement to neglect her and her position. As a senior manager myself, I see value in her role. The task itself becomes challenging as it is all about repitions day in day out. If everyone could do this, they already wouldve. The times I frequent this establishment while shes away or after her shift, the condiments etc are always EMPTY. Thank you for hiring her so us customer can constantly have straws, lids, condiments at our disposal. A little goes a long. Hope this translates / transpires into a wage increase for her. I will be acknowledging her that Ive left this review to have her be recognize. You store managers should do the same.
How it looks like during COVID-19 in the dinning area.

Come here pretty regularly. Drive thru service is always quick. Prices on some items are a little cheaper than some of the other Mcd restaurants in the area. Never had an issue with curbside pickup either. The dining-in experience is above average compared to other locations. I have come here for years, and plan to continue for years to come
Busy and good place to drink coffee. It has nice parking place to park your car.

This McDonalds has the best night drive thru in the world! The server is hilarious, engaging, prompt and Im pretty sure he threw in a heel click with glee when he ran outside to deliver my food. Thanks dude for brightening my evening!
Huge seating area including second floor with play area. Amazing kids loved it Food : 5/5

McDonald s has been really proactive with COVID-19 safety. Prior to the pandemic their restaurants were among the cleanest fast food places. Now they are even cleaner. The food is predictable and the coffee is really quite good.

Depending on the staff that are on shift, this McDonalds gives me faith in humanity. The food is always fresh here and usually really good. Havent messed up my order yet. The people taking your order arent brick walls. Never had an unreasonable wait here. Overall a stellar example of what all McDonalds should aspire to be.

This is one of the better McDonald s with a really nice large dine-in area on the second floor and clean washrooms (with no weird people squatting the booths). It s a little out of the way and only accessible by driving probably

This location is the best. Heard it was the head office (in BC? Not sure). There are some staff members who aren t very considerate listeners when it comes to customers with accents or lower English language proficiency (my folks have been felt shunned for their English... luckily for them, I wasn t there ), but most of the times the staff there are friendly. They are cool with giving condiments (as some places will charge you), and their second floor area is a lovely place to sit and just chill.  Parking is free, but watch-out as some lots are now designated for other businesses there.
I dropped my ice cream but they gave a replacement one! Great customer service at this location.

Good McDonalds location. The servers are really nice, and the food comes out really quickly. Well organized, and very clean. I havent had any problems with this one. The food is very well made, for McDonalds quality.

This is probably one of the largest McDonalds Ive ever visit. It has two stories and LOTS of seats. Food came real quick and we enjoyed the stay. Though it is not that convenient to visit if you dont have a car, but you can pretty much enjoy McDonalds anywhere else too.
Makes me feel good to be here. The staffs are peppy and upbeat. Never had a wrong order. The whole system is like a well oiled machine. Good job! I always love coming here instead of other McDonalds.

Great, clean restaurant that is one of the most elegant McDonalds restaurant Ive been so far. It doesnt really look like a fast food chain from the outside, ample parking and drive thru service is fast as well. There are mobile app parking stalls as well if you are in a hurry to get food.
Was there at 12:30 on Thursday, during lunch Rush, the Lady on Till was amazing, taking drive through orders, running for her self and giving every customer the best service.
Had an issue with a mobile order and they resolved it quickly and even gave me the sandwiches for free since something went wrong on the app end. Their manager was helpful and very friendly.
Friendly and timely service. We came in ordered something like 8 breakfast burger and sides and the staff were patient and attentive. Would definitely come again of I am in the area.

Went too this location for lunch, lady was at the door only letting a few people order at a time the ketchup pumps were also taken away. Really nice bike path/paved trail right across from this mc donalds.
This is one time they didnt screw up our order. Are they getting better? Only time will tell.

Updated: January 13, 2019 I had the pleasure of dealing with Sarah the manager. She was fantastic and has earned a 5 star review Old:It s rarely up to par here. Just sad because it s head office. This his always been drive thru servive. I did go in once. It s super nice inside, tv, upstairs lounge fireplace. Nice stuff.

Surinder in the drive thru is always a delight. She takes my order promptly, professionally and with a smile. After paying for my morning coffee her words of  thank you dear  always starts my day on a positive note. Give that woman a raise!

McDonalds is trying a new system. Today, we went to the McDonalds on Willingdon, near the freeway. We ordered and were given a disc to take to a table that allowed a staff member to find our table and bring our food to us. After our food arrived, a staff member followed up to be sure everything was fine. It was nice to not have to hang around in the ordering area, waiting for our food.
Kudos to the Manager/Supervisor of this branch for finding my wallet that I left on the couch! I am so thankful she found it and kept it in a safe place!

Located in a calm area in North Burnaby, this Mc Donalds has lots of space for parking, online pick-ups, accessible park spots, short lines for the drive-thru and a great view if you want to dine-in in the mezzanine. Its my favorite Mc Donalds in the region, by far.
Best McDonalds Ive been in. Above average service, personable staff, very clean restaurant, food was exactly to order, hot and fresh. A refreshing experience, thank you!
Hi, our recent visit proved to be worthy, fries were perfect and so was my filet o fish.

Ordered a pot of coffee muffins and danishes werent ready waiting waiting and waiting make me late for work this is the new online ordering and pickup service not sure when its going to be a good hopefully McDonalds respond by a couple extra muffins while I wait here..... well went back that day an they gave me full refund just what I wanted ... went and tried it the next day and it was way better thanks McD s good job
So good

The Mcdonalds headquarters for Canada I think. Service is always fast and quality of food pretty much the peak of what you can get from McDonalds. It would make sense as this is where corporate eyes are always watching and people are training to the McDonalds Gold Standard. Great place to hang out while waiting for car-related stuff at the nearby dealerships.
5/5. Classic. Timeless. Reliable. McDonalds never disappoints be it breakfast, lunch, dinner or an illicit but desperately necessary 11pm stroll through the drivethrough. Cant go wrong.
Rated in the drive through, easy, quick and efficient. No comment on the food, its what you would expect. Vegetarian options: Sold options Parking: Lots of room

This is the best McDonalds experience in the area. Large restaurant with upstairs and outdoor seating. Music plays throughout (outside too, theres even a fireplace outside to keep you warm!) I also appreciate the 24/7 service.

The service is like all Mcdicks, hit or miss, mostly hit. The restaurant however is freaking awesome, its huge, if you stay downstairs you may think it sucks but once you go upstairs there is always sitting space and they have tvs upstairs too. On the downside as an adult with no kids, they also have a whole playground upstairs and sometimes the kids are loud, but overall, this Macdonald is a nice one to go to.
Great location, good number of parking spots available. Staff are friendly and service is reasonably fast. I never have trouble finding a spot to eat even during the busiest hours.
Charlotte is the best. Very kind and amazing customer service. She deserves a promotion.
This MacDonalds has one of the best environments in Vancouver. The outside patio has a good open view of the surrounding landscaping. The inside has a fireplace and lots of natural light.
They made my sandwich quick and it tasted great, better than normal mcdonalds. I tried the chicken mcgriddle and it was blessed. Definitely reccomend it. I put lettuce and mayo on mine.
A great place to grab a meal. Our order was correct, hot and tasted great. The Staff were very friendly and quick to accommodate our requests. Thanks McDs
Real good service. The staff were most excellent.!  The manager actually made me smile. And was uplifting. I hope you go places Sir..   thank-you for all Ure kindness i really needed it today..!
Like any other McDonalds. Drive thru staff were really friendly. Fast service.
Flagship store, at least when it opened. Quick, efficient with friendly and very well trained staff. Food also finest McQuality.
This McDonalds is nicely maintained and clean.  Food is typical McDonalds, its ok and not bad.  There are plenty of sitting spaces.  They even deliver the good to your table.
Still Creek Dr. Is THE  BEST  McDonalds to order from , great crew always follow instructions and food is amazing. These people ROCK !!! Keep up the great work. Cheers
My son loves their newly renovated play area!   Service was great!  They didnt get mad at me for order a burger with mobile service.  :-P

Great Mc Donalds location. Clean, spacious, 2 floors with a kids play area in the top floor.  Friendly staff. Meal was tasty and fresh, complying with the high-quality standards of the Mc Donalds chain. My kids love that place.
Always got my orders right and drive thru most time faster then inside. Clean and large sitting area.

I ordered a double quarter pounder meal from the self-serve kiosk. I sat down at a table, and placed my receipt showing my order number facing up. After a few minutes, I saw an employee cruising around close to me with what looked like my meal. After some minutes more, I went to the counter to enquire after my order. The clerk gave it to me. I sat down to enjoy it, but it was ice-cold. I took it back up to the counter, and told them. The clerk asked me if I had placed my receipt on the counter next to me, and I told him I had. He said that he would remake it for me. I went and sat down again. After a few minutes, he brought it out, gave it to me, and apologized for the mistake. The meal was hot and tasty, just like youd expect from McDonalds. They turned a negative customer experience into a positive one! Well done!

McDonalds is one of the most popular fast-food chains around the world, including Canada, and it is known for its french fries and various menu options. The McDonalds branch located in Guildford mall, Canada, is a typical restaurant, serving the classic McDonalds menu items, including burgers, fries, chicken nuggets, and other fast-food options. Regarding its chocolate donut, McDonalds offers a variety of classic bakery items, such as muffins, croissants, and donuts. Their chocolate donut is one of their popular items and is enjoyed by many customers. Overall, McDonalds Guildford mall is a reliable choice for fast-food options, and their chocolate donut and french fries are worth a try. However, it is also essential to be mindful of ones dietary and health needs while consuming fast foods.

Ok, so I have had a very bad day today and after not having anything all day, I went to this place to have a Mac chicken meal. The first time I got my order, I wasn t satisfied with my burger and coffee so I went in and ordered a second one. The girl told me I don t have to pay but I insisted on paying cuz I ate the burger already.  The second one I ordered I told them make sure there s no Mac chicken sauce but I got sauce in it again.  I tried to go back to drive thru to complain my coffee spilled all over my car.  So I went inside and talked to the manager, who was not very sympathetic so I just walked away and started cleaning my car outside.  I saw $10 on the ground, I picked it up, asked the guys if it s theirs but they said no. By the ways my meal costed me about the exact same amount.  Within a few mins, a really sweet girl, exactly like an  angel  came out with the money in her hand for my meal and a towel to help me clean my car. Omg I mean how this girl changed my whole day!! I can t describe it ... she was insisting on cleaning my rug and told me tat there s a new order coming up for me. She was so nice and sweet that I felt bad about the whole situation. She comforted me hugged me, and so I was curious wat is she?? asked her name, she said her name is Miriam, and she is from Iraq. I stopped myself after she left and started thinking about; if everybody was like her, there would not be any racism, any fights, nor any trouble in this world. I m sure the manager sent her to make sure I leave happy but she went way beyond anyone s expectations. I m in the same field myself for more then 15 years but I don t think I have done or seen anything like this before. I really want to thank all the members of this McDonald s, specially Miriam for making my day !!!

Annacis Island has alot of warehousing rather than retail business so clientel is 99% warehouse workers,truck drivers and office staff. So its different in a nice way...lts not that I dont like children or old people..we all will be that ,if we live long enough ,but your not going to see much of them here. So if you want full spectrum of the population go Mcds at Metrotown and youll see what I mean. So no review about the food quality..only the coffee..l love Mcds coffee Haha!  Jim from Vancouver.

As far as McDonalds go, this is one of the best ive experience in a long time. It is Nov 13th 2016 in the afternoon. Its not terribly busy, theres 2 floors with the upstairs hosting one of the rare play places, and the service is on point. I walked in, saw the digital ordering kiosks. I love how amazingly powerful they are. Dont forget that you can tap on an order and hit Customize to go crazy with the most granular possible nit picky stuff you can think of.  Today the Build Your Taste burger builder was fully integrated and let me absolutely get the details I wanted. Once the order was complete it got me to pick up an elecronic device known as a Table Tracker, this allowed me to bring my kid upstairs to the play place with my number and pretty close after ordering two gentlemen came upstairs with my order on a wooden paddle, and my daughters happy meal carried separately and carefully. The men asked us if we wanted any condiments, to which we asked for ketchup to which they happily obliged. No restaurant, especially fast food, has evolved over time quite like McDonalds. I though McCafe was a pretty big deal when it came around but now McDonalds seems to be catering to thise who want real food, with real service one could experience at a standard family restaurant.  Except i dont have to wait 35 minutes to an hour gor my order to come about. I imagine it wont be like this all the time, in fact im pretty sure to expect just like what happened to FatBurger. Sure everyones enthusiastic now, give it a month and some change and well be back to old habbits. But for now, I will remember the excellent service and encourage it where I can.

Accessibility Information - This review was prepared by my Social Studies 9 class after a site visit and an interview with the manager. We went to local McDonalds located in 15574 Fraser Hwy to find out if this McDonalds was accessible for people who use wheelchairs or scooters. We were able to find things that made this place accessible. First, there were two accessible parking spots available right beside the entrance to the store. Second, the doors of the store could be opened by pressing a button that is placed on the wall beside the door. There is a ramp for wheelchairs and scooters to go up. Also, they are planning to get new doors so that it is easier for wheelchair and scooter users to use. The bathroom doors do not have buttons on the wall, but the sink, the toilet paper, the dryer, and the soap were placed low so that they can be easily accessed by wheelchair and scooter users. The aisles in the restaurant are wide enough for wheelchair and scooter users to go through.

I normally wouldn t write a review for mcdonald s because they re all pretty much the same, but I just wanted to leave one for one lady that works the drive thru. I ve been going through an emotional time the past few days because of my dog being very sick, & even though she has no idea, she has been such a ray of sunshine & has made my day. I went through the drive thru twice in the past few days to get a drink because it s near the vet clinic my dog s been at & both times she has been absolutely lovely. I don t know her name, but today she was wearing some blue gloves underneath the plastic latex gloves that all the staff wear. Both today & Monday (both times ~10am) she was at the second window as well. Please let her know that she is wonderful & her kindness has meant the world to me

My family and I come to this location quite often and always use the drive though. We have always had such wonderful experiences when we are served by Sheryl. This is my local McDonalds on a busy intersection a few kms from my home.  When cv19 hit I was really big and decided to intermittent fast and choose a keto designed lifestyle.  I never drank coffee before but now needed to due to my fasting. So each day 5 days a week around 6:30am I drive to order my xtra large coffee for 2.40$ and get a couple butters to put into it which helps me stave off hunger till I break my fast at 11am. The staff is amazing and I always collect the tiny sticker to get my almost free xtra large on the 8th visit. I should double dip on the points I havent yet maybe I will do so soon. Staff is great, quick and look forward to a smile and a have a great day...it is almost like Im harkened back to Mulberry in the 50s they are so nice.

Went there late at night/early in the morning (depending on your perspective), dude named Nathan, looked kinda funny and was a bit short, made my meal lickity split, gave him a fist bump and a kiss on the cheek. Best Customer Service Ever!!!!

Waited a long time in line due to another customer getting refunds etc  ...when we got to our turn the manager apologized to which we said..no problem at all . After we finished ordering our meals the manager said it was on her ! Totally unexpected and very well done...thank you !!

As we all know McDonalds food is pretty much the same everywhere, however I give this location a 5 due to the consistency over the past couple years of the morning crew in their great service. Over the past couple years even though my visits could be sometimes a few weeks apart the drive thru always moves quickly when getting coffee never having to wait for so long unlike some other locations. Its always the same morning crew who are courteous, and efficient in moving customers through the line up which means they are organized in the kitchen, and have a great team leader. If you are in a hurry in the morning but need that coffee/quick breakfast this location is perfect. You dont have to wait as if they are cooking a Thanksgiving turkey.

So, here I am, once again reviewing a McDonalds... but... Im actually recommending this one this time! I feel like this should go against my code...however hear me out! Their egg McMuffins...are actually made with a freshly cracked egg...and at this particular McDonalds...they cook them to PERFECTION!! Its got the slightest bit of runny yolk left, sausage cooked without being burned or rubbery and the cheese is actually tasty! All this however pales in comparison to the cheery, smiley, joyful ladies who greet you on the microphone, take your order, send you ahead, and then with a smile so big that can be seen through their mask, hand you a breakfast that tastes so good, it can only be because it was crafted with love.... Im LOVING IT XD

I head to this location after 12am-3am when I m drunk (my sober gf driving).you ll often see review of  drive through is slow blah blah blah etc  some people don t understand they have a system reboot which results in the delay but that s besides the point. Everytime I come by at such a late hour and always asking for a picky order ie  made fresh please  I have been welcomed with politeness and gratitude for my order. Some people are always polite and nice even working nights shift (beats me, I ve done it and I m a monster during those hours).nonetheless to my surprise, not only was the male who was getting off at 3am was super polite with my order and payment but as I rolled to the last window to pick up my order (you can tell this lady was tired) she was polite, gracious and  patient as I check the bag for the sauces to my delicious nuggets that were made fresh (I know this cause while we were digging through the order it was hot af [she told us  don t burn your hands ]) she didn t make a fuss but told us have a good night after. They all deserve a raise and i send my utmost gratitude for their work (hope they see this) and attitude during the graveyard shift. Thanks guys, I made sure to drop by this one while I drove by other McDonald s on the way home. To the owner, they deserve a raise if not, at least a gift card for their consistent service. I devoured my freshly made cheeseburger (delicious btw) but thought I d post something to legitimize my review. :)

I gave a very negative review regarding the quality of the food, the level of customer service at this location about one year ago. It was warranted.  It was terrible. For the past 2 months I ve been coming back here late at night, everything has changed.   They tell you to wait a few mins for your order but that s because they are cooking it fresher for you. Even though it seems they are still understaffed at times, the STAFF is putting in the effort to make each and every order the way it should be.  Fresh, hot and with a smile. Dear owner and managers, I know margins are very low right now but please try to do your best to have enough staff on to help them do their jobs better and also happier. Keep up the good work and thanks for doing a great job serving your local community!

The ambiance is typical McDs, & the interior had a major renovation recently. Seniors enjoying their discount coffee & Trades workers picking up a fast lunch.

The food was divine. Kudos to the chefs. Only one thing, though, that s I found weird about this restaurant. There was a man lurking in the corner of the the restaurant  I took a seat across from him, introduced myself, and he told me folks called him the Bush Man. He seemed to be a rather kind man, though a bit mysterious. We seemed to have ordered the same thing  a McDouble meal, large fries, and large Diet Coke. He told me,  Don t trust that maidens will find you, you must find them yourself.  I was reading through other reviews and noticed other stuff had a similar experience. Weird. Uncanny.

I met a man here who called himself The Bush Man. We both ordered the same item: Double Cheeseburger with Large Fries. Upon us sitting down, he leaned forward and told me something of which I had never forgotten: Dont Trust that Maidens will find you. You must look for them yourself. Upon him completing his sentence, he was gone. Meal and All. But his wisdom in which he bestowed me... it was nearly better than the meal I had. 10/10, I am enlightened.

Theres a couple of women who regularly work the morning shift at the drive thru windows. One takes payment, the other gives you your order. They are awesome. Friendly, smiling, upbeat and a pleasure to see each time we would grab a coffee or breakfast. I give them 5 stars But in the evenings the kids working are robotic, impersonal, and do not exhibit the friendly helpful manners of customer service. The ice cream machines always broken. I cant get less ice in my drink, even when i request it. The cold drinks have more ice than soda, yet mcdonalds limits the drink orders because they dont have enough ice. It was hot out, we were all thirsty, and only 4 out of five of us were allowed to buy a drink. I couldnt order any cold drink even if I didnt want ice in mine. If mcdonalds used less ice in the fountain drinks, customers could get enough liquid to wash down their meal, and they could hydrate more customers. But they dont have what their signs have advertising 60% of the time. Gets frustrating

Brian, who just served us at 11:39pm on November 5th, was absolutely amazing. My family has lived by this McDonalds since it first opened in the early 2000s. The atmosphere here was less than amazing for quite some time but for a little while now I noticed a massive shift in the demeanor and friendliness of the workers. I understand this kind of job can be incredibly difficult and it can be really thankless. Some people are just horrible to service workers. I always try to respect that as much as I can. It takes a special kind of person to elevate the environment in a situation like that and Brian has done exactly that. I hope someone important sees this and ensures he receives the recognition he deserves.

The space is TINY on the first floor but you can go up the steepest most narrow steps possible to get to the second floor where there is more seating. Despite the small size, this Mc Donald s is located in a small plaza with the tightest parking spots possible. The staff were helpful and friendly although as many have stated, if there s a few people in line you are out the door. There are two self-serve screens inside and a small bathroom on the ground floor. There are also two small tables at the front of the first floor but 5 outdoor tables. There s a sign that says personal reusable cups are encouraged and also a sign outdoors that says outdoor seating is for patrons only. However I saw many sitting here enjoying their non-Mc Donalds lunch. I liked seeing people utilize their outdoor seating and the community feel it brought so bravo for allowing others to sit and use your tables, I really liked seeing this and 5 stars and this review just for that.

I want to start off by saying, I have experience dining at fast food restaurants throughout my college and university years. The Panorama location, in my opinion is not only the most pleasant McDonalds location that I have experience but the most pleasant fast food restaurant that I know of. The staff is super friendly and the location is very clean on a consistent basis. The manager working, Earin has an excellent attitude and I can see she leads her entire staff by example. I eat here often and there are times when its busy and the manager keeps her cool and you can see the confidence in her and her team. I also see that the organization takes their customers serious by their recognition of adding a better drive through. Overall, I think I speak for alot of others when I say, this McDonalds location is a great part of the community and the people that work here should be recognized for their efforts. Especially the management team. Thanks. Roy

Manager Parm and her team were very professional and swift to help me deal with my issues. With the current pandemic going on, it s understandable if the staffs were as stressed as customers like me, but all of them treated me with care and respect, which I appreciate very much and want to let people know about it. This is my first time having issues with McDonald s in general, but isn t the first time I experienced high level of attention and care from the staffs of this McDonald s location. From other places, I experienced and understood there s always a certain SOP to satisfy (upset) customers and handle situations like this, but the professional and careful attitudes makes all the difference. Whoever s reading this comment; wether you are from regional management or local staff, as long as you are related to this McDonald s location, I want you to know, the neighborhood and I appreciate you and your hard work very much. Sincerely, -Ian, the guy with face mask.

I recently had the pleasure of dining at McDonalds and indulging in their famous Big Mac meal. Let me just say, I was thoroughly convinced that this fast-food chain knows how to deliver a satisfying and delicious experience. The Big Mac meal truly lives up to its reputation. The moment I unwrapped the iconic burger, I was greeted by a mouthwatering aroma that instantly made my taste buds dance with anticipation. The perfectly toasted sesame seed bun held together two juicy beef patties, topped with the signature Big Mac sauce, crisp lettuce, tangy pickles, and melted cheese. Every bite was a symphony of flavors that left me wanting more. What impressed me the most was the consistency in the quality of the Big Mac meal. No matter which McDonalds location I visit, I can always count on the same great taste and satisfaction. This level of reliability is a testament to their commitment to delivering a consistently delicious product. In addition to the incredible taste, the value for money at McDonalds is unbeatable. The Big Mac meal offers a generous portion size that leaves you feeling fully satisfied without breaking the bank. Its the perfect option for a quick and affordable meal that doesnt compromise on taste or quality. The service at McDonalds is also worth mentioning. The staff members are always friendly, efficient, and ready to assist with any requests. Whether its customizing your order or providing recommendations, they go above and beyond to ensure a pleasant dining experience. Overall, McDonalds has truly mastered the art of the Big Mac meal. The combination of mouthwatering flavors, consistent quality, and excellent service make it a go-to choice for a quick and satisfying meal. If youre looking for a fast-food option that never disappoints, I highly recommend giving McDonalds a try. You wont be disappointed!

This review is for the employee Justine. Ive been to this location many times. It often feels a little depressing when you walk in the door and you can see it in the staffs demeanor. One day I walked in for a cold dessert and encountered the bubbliest, happiest, the most joyful employee I have ever encountered. Even with her mask on, I can tell she was smiling ear to ear as she took my order. It felt very welcoming and it was a nice change. The way she would communicate with her coworkers, with so much respect and care, showed me that her demeanor is genuine. The amount of joy she was putting out was radiating throughout the place and I picked up on it. I was having a long day (hence why I came in for the dessert) and she totally changed my mood. Justine is going places and making a lot of people happy in the process. If management sees this review please let Justine know how much of a difference she is making at your location. Its not just the food that makes an establishment stand out.

In 1967, the first McDonalds Canada opened in Richmond, B.C. Weve been growing with our communities and serving quality food at great value ever since. Today, McDonalds Canada is proud to be one of the worlds leading food service retailers. In June 1967, businessman George Tidball brought the McDonalds chain to Canada after buying Western Canada rights from the American corporation for a $50,000 down payment. Tidball got his inspiration while on a road trip to California, where he visited the McDonalds headquarters.

Updated review: Perhaps my last review sparked something here because their attitude and listening skills improved. I used to get breakfast here a couple of times a week and eventually one of the ladies started recognising me and remembering my order and I would usually just have to confirm between two items that I always ordered. I am now working from home so I no longer go there, but I sometimes miss my little routine and receiving great customer service! Previous review: This is one of the worst locations Ive been to in Vancouver.  There are two women here that are part of the morning crew who give the most horrendous service I have ever experienced and one of them is a supervisor/manager. They dont know how to listen and as a result they get my order wrong...often. Theres nothing complicated about ordering a McMuffin without cheese and two hashbrowns. When I order coffee, they get the size or number of creams wrong. This isnt Starbucks and Im not ordering a complicated drink but somehow a simple cup of coffee gets messed up almost every time. They often ring in my order wrong and I have to repeat myself two or three times before they get it right and they like to argue with me as if Im doing something wrong. I speak perfect English and they seem to as well, but clearly their listening skills are lacking.

After being thoroughly soaked in the Vancouver dreadful weather, we were immediately cheered by the warm welcoming smile of your employee Colin. He was so helpful as I had lost my glasses and couldnt read the board, so he talked us through the options and prices and informed us of the combos, as well as the current monopoly promotion. Its good to see there are still kind young people today.

review_text: Ordered breakfast this morning and I was one of the first to arrive. Ordered my usual but now its not edible because the bagel is stale. Its a hockey puck. Thank you to the manager.

First time here and the restaurant had a weird layout of 3 compact floors not any other Mcdonalds in Metro Vancouver. This place is not meant for elderly or people disabilities going up stairs to find seating on the 2nd or 3rd floor.

I have genuinely have no idea about the 1 star reviews but Ill take it, for what I know, our experience here was completely normal, this is by far for what I know, one of the McDonalds with the biggest kitchen Ive ever seen. Gives us less space but the upstairs seating gives a bit more space to make up for it, for some reason the waiting area for your order is small, and gives less space for a dine in, overall I wouldnt say its bad and one my favourites, its just a fast food chain there that exists. Also Ive noticed that their not open 24/7, which is stupid by me, overall I think you should go outside to the fountain and eat there, but I think were lucky we got upstairs.

This is the prettiest and most technological McDonalds Ive been to so far. They even have handicapped door buttons you can use your foot! (I want to give a 5 star just for that. Its so cool!) But it was really small, and they close the upper floor at night. But the reason Im giving a 3 star was because the staff gave us spoons for our icecream, and put it ON THE COUNTER. Where cash, coins and peoples hands TOUCH. I worked at multiple food industry places. If he did that in my workplace, he wouldve gotten fired immediately. I hope the other staff have basic food safe knowledge, and training because that alone is a huge red flag. (I ended up asking for 2 more spoons instead of grabbing it from the counter)

Good quality here, and accurate ordering. Ive never had any negative expereinces here as far as the food goes. The service is good, and they are friendly, however it is a small location and does get busy a lot of the time. And lines of even 4 or 5 people can be significantly long, especially while going during lunch. As for the morning, they have had no hashbrowns quite a few times that I have gone for breakfast during my break. They stopped giving out napkins at the self-serve drink dispensers and you have to go to the counter to ask for them, which is a bit strange. But apart from those few things, this location is good. And like I said, Ive never had any food related issues, which is more than I can say about a lot of other locations.
